  "body": "- [X ] I've [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI tried following the Truffle Tezos Quickstart Guide on both a Windows machine and a Linux machine, and I get the same compilation error with no additional information. I filed a support request and they eventually said to file an issue here.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nI followed the guide here: https://www.trufflesuite.com/docs/tezos/truffle/quickstart\r\nI made sure NodeJS and Docker were installed. I installed the Tezos version of Truffle. I unboxed the tezos-example project. Then I ran \"truffle compile\". On both systems (Linux/Windows) I get an identical error message.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\n```\r\nCompiling your contracts... \r\n=========================== \r\n> Compiling ./contracts/Counter.ligo \r\n> Compiling ./contracts/Migrations.ligo \r\n> Compiling ./contracts/SimpleStorage.ligo \r\n> Using entry point \"main\" \r\nWarning: The old cli is deprecated, use `ligo --help` or `ligo man` to consult the new command syntax \r\n\r\nCompilation of /home/gabriel/repos/tezos-example/contracts/Counter.ligo failed. See above. \r\nTruffle v5.5.0-tezos.4 (core: 5.5.0-tezos.4) \r\nNode v14.17.6 \r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't see any error message other than the warning about the \"old cli...\". When I do \"ligo --help\" or \"ligo man\" it's not recognized in either system. What is supposed to install the ligo cli?\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System:  Windows 10 and Linux (Ubuntu)\r\nTruffle v5.5.0-tezos.4 (core: 5.5.0-tezos.4) \r\nNode v14.17.6 \r\nnpm v7.24.1\r\n![Screenshot 2021-09-24 170912](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4461804/134740004-8b99da8f-f862-4f52-bffc-d5a36db9a0f8.png)\r\n\r\n![Screenshot 2021-09-24 171722](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4461804/134740707-47fc3ea8-a735-4079-8f7f-3a7dd54f7c01.png)\r\n",
