    "body": "This is an issue of incompatibility with the new CLI of the LIGO compiler.\r\n\r\nIn the `execLigo` function, the call to LIGO should become something like:\r\n```\r\n        var docker = child_process_1.spawn(\"docker\", [\r\n            \"run\",\r\n            \"-v\",\r\n            currentWorkingDirectory + \":/project\",\r\n            \"--rm\",\r\n            \"-i\",\r\n            \"ligolang/ligo:next\",\r\n            \"compile\",\r\n            \"contract\",\r\n            fullInternalSourcePath,\r\n            \"--michelson-format\",\r\n            \"json\",\r\n            \"-e\",\r\n            entryPoint\r\n        ]);\r\n```\r\n\r\n(althought it'd be good if warning messages in `stderr` would not be considered fatal errors anymore)\r\n\r\n> I don't see any error message other than the warning about the \"old cli...\". When I do \"ligo --help\" or \"ligo man\" it's not recognized in either system. What is supposed to install the ligo cli?\r\n\r\nIf you want to run LIGO directly, you can run it via `docker`:\r\n```\r\ndocker run --rm -v \"$PWD\":\"$PWD\" -w \"$PWD\" ligolang/ligo:next man\r\n```\r\n(for Linux; similar for Windows, see here: https://ligolang.org/docs/intro/installation/#dockerised-installation-recommended)",
